From: Vasu Bhatia <git@vbh.ai>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 12:58:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 13/13] eink: silence AOSP auto-brightness when SystemUI
 controller owns it

EinkAutoBrightnessController in SystemUI drives cold/warm/keyboard from
inverted curves keyed off the ambient light sensor. AOSP's own auto-
brightness path would also try to write screen_brightness_float on every
sensor tick using a curve that goes the wrong direction for e-ink.

Gate the existing auto-brightness apply in DisplayPowerController on the
read-only system property ro.eink.auto_owns_brightness (set true in our
product makefile). When the property is true and brightness mode is
AUTOMATIC, AOSP's automatic strategy is short-circuited and our SystemUI
controller is the sole driver.

Change-Id: I7f46c29dcb6f36b39d0cbb01928e2b932c485bfb
---
 .../android/server/display/DisplayPowerController.java   | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/services/core/java/com/android/server/display/DisplayPowerController.java b/services/core/java/com/android/server/display/DisplayPowerController.java
index e913ddbf50d0..c12357aa4d0a 100644
--- a/services/core/java/com/android/server/display/DisplayPowerController.java
+++ b/services/core/java/com/android/server/display/DisplayPowerController.java
@@ -53,6 +53,7 @@ import android.os.HandlerExecutor;
 import android.os.IBinder;
 import android.os.Looper;
 import android.os.Message;
+import android.os.SystemProperties;
 import android.os.PowerManager;
 import android.os.RemoteException;
 import android.os.SystemClock;
@@ -1507,7 +1508,13 @@ final class DisplayPowerController implements AutomaticBrightnessController.Call
             // AutomaticBrightnessStrategy has higher priority than OffloadBrightnessStrategy
             if (Float.isNaN(brightnessState)
                     || mBrightnessReasonTemp.getReason() == BrightnessReason.REASON_OFFLOAD) {
-                if (mAutomaticBrightnessStrategy.isAutoBrightnessEnabled()) {
+                // E-ink: SystemUI's EinkAutoBrightnessController drives cold/warm/keyboard
+                // from custom inverted curves. Skip AOSP's auto path so the two systems
+                // don't both try to write screen_brightness_float on every sensor tick.
+                final boolean einkAutoOwnsBrightness =
+                        SystemProperties.getBoolean("ro.eink.auto_owns_brightness", false);
+                if (mAutomaticBrightnessStrategy.isAutoBrightnessEnabled()
+                        && !einkAutoOwnsBrightness) {
                     brightnessState = mAutomaticBrightnessStrategy.getAutomaticScreenBrightness(
                             mTempBrightnessEvent);
                     if (BrightnessUtils.isValidBrightnessValue(brightnessState)
